args:
With Tsukuyomi weakened, Amaterasu appears,
entrusts the land to Yukimura and the others,
and elects mutual annihilation with Tsukuyomi.
A new year and a new peace then arrive,
but Hinomotoan loyalty remains unchanged.
Fly, spear, and pierce that dark heart!
How dare you lowly humans put a scratch\non me!
But know this: Even without Yomi chi,\nI am a noble dragon! A wound such as\nthis is nothing to me!
Even that wasn't enough to beat her?!\nFine then! We just do it again!
I thank you, children of man. Your valiant\nstruggle has drained Tsukuyomi of much\nof her strength.
Enough so that even without form,\nI can achieve her end with my own.
My Lady, what are you saying?!
In truth, the War of Earth and Heaven\nought to have ended thus.
We two are sisters, born from the same chi\nof the ancestral dragons. It was folly to let\npity stay my hand from duty.
You claim leaving me alive was an act of\nmercy? That it was mercy which drove\nyou to lock me in that accursed cave?!
It was, but no longer. Though we share\nthe same chi, you are a thing corruptâ€”\nand we are sisters no more.
To safeguard the people of this land\nnow and forever more...
I will put a proper end to the\nWar of Earth and Heaven!
Lady Amaterasu herself is unmaking\nthis very world.
But that's the whole of Amaterasu's \nremaining power! If it is lost...
Is Amaterasu truly planning to take\nherself down with Tsukuyomi?
Please, Lady Amaterasu, you must not\ndo this thing! I beg you to stop!
Do not stay me from this, Izumo.\nMy life has long been all but lost.
Your kind has shepherded Hinomoto well\nin the long years without me.
And I know you will preserve its peace\nhenceforth. Do you not agree?
And I will ever be your emissary and\ncarry on your will and word.
The other Wyrmclan leaders and I will\nall do our part to keep this land safe.\nWon't we, General?!
I haven't much time left before age takes\nme, but I will pass what strength I have on\nto the next generation.
Another row of the tapestry woven.\nJust as you said, Lady Amaterasu, this\nunbroken chain is mankind's true strength.
I am at peace to hear it. Go, then.\nReturn to the realm of the living.
You and I are as ghosts of a world long\nsince passed, Tsukuyomi.
I go on to join the great flow of chi,\nand I shall have you at my side!
Unhand me! Let go, I say!
I entrust the rest to you,\nmy beloved people.

Days had passed by the time we returned from
Takamagaharaâ€”the lag a curious byproduct of
the forced teleportation, perhapsâ€”and a new
year had come.
We arrived to find Hinomoto still in chaos,\nbut the threat of Tsukuyomi and the evil she\nunleashed had passed.
Without a leader, the Mukuroshu quickly fell into\ndisarray. Its remnants still walk free for now, but\nHinomoto's peace has been preserved this day.
Seeds of unrest remain, and the coming\nage will see great change in Hinomoto.
The shogun's pactbound dragon is no more,\nand none can say how Lady Amaterasu's\npassing will reverberate.
But the shogunate still has the Wyrmclans,\nand I will wield the power of my soulpact\nto support it always.
I hope to do the same. Let us protect this\nland with all of our strength combined.
Followed along again, have you, Yuki?\nYou know you should be resting.
I can walk just fine, so I'm feeling GREAT!
But anyway, I need your help with\ntoday's lesson!
And here I'd thought you'd already become\na fully-fledged Wyrmclan leader. You still\nrequire my lessons?
Of course! Training is a lifelong pursuit.\nand there's plenty left in that gruff heart\nof yours that I want to know.
Ha ha! A fine show of resolve indeed!\nCome then, Yuki. I'll not hold back just\nbecause you're still recovering.
*sigh* That pair is as sweaty as ever.\nAnd with Lady Yukimura still hurt too.
I wish she would just hurry up and let\nLord Shingen go.
Whoa! What's with the new look,\n{player_name}?
I picked it up it here in Hinomoto.\nPart of a little idea I had.
Oh? And what might that be?
Well, I thought maybe WE could be the\nones to deliver blessings this year!
We could never be so bold! Not after all\nof your help with Tsukuyomi.
Hey, that's what pals are for! Plus, I know\nthings are still pretty bonkers in Hinomoto,\nso c'mon. Let us help out.
You've made the long trip to deliver us\nblessings for years now; this is the perfect\nchance for us to return the favor.
Just that... Well, the one who first\nconceived of the tradition of delivering\nblessings was Lady Amaterasu.
She hoped we might foster good relations\nwith other lands that would help us all\nenjoy a brighter future.
And you know what? She was right.\nIt brought us allies willing to come to\nour aid in times of need.
Sounds exactly right to me! I bet seeing\npeople from different places working\ntogether is just what Amaterasu wanted.
Hear that, General? We're trading places\nfor this year's blessing delivery!
I look forward to seeing what this\nprince from New Alberia can do.
Leave it to us! Now then, if I may...
